Corrections  Amplifications
---
   KROGER Co. will "call" as much as $100 million of its
high-yield debt. An earlier edition incorrectly characterized
the company's intentions.
   (See: "Kroger to Buy Back Debt" -- WSJ Feb. 20, 1992)
   ---
   REALTY REFUND TRUST's annual and quarterly results were
misstated in an earlier edition. A corrected table appears
{in this issue}.
   ---
   ROYAL APPLIANCES MANUFACTURING Co.'s 1991 fourth-quarter
sales were $112,191,000, compared with year-earlier sales of
$53,309,000. Because of a computer error, an earlier edition
transposed the figures.